{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "• Self-Refine (SR): SR (Madaan et al., 2023) is a type of iterative process of prompting the LLM with a set of instructions.",
    "The main idea is to instruct the LLM to continuously provide feedback for its' own output and refine using the feedback, the process stops when the feedback deems the output as sufficient in solving the task at hand.",
    "The whole iterative process is achieved by self-prompting the same language model.",
    "There exist other forms of acquiring feedback, such as querying a trained feedback model or using external factual knowledge (Pan et al., 2023).",
    "We choose the approach of querying the same LLM as we are focused on the explainability of generated outputs from a sole LLM."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "• Self-Refine (SR): SR (Madaan et al., 2023) is a type of iterative process of prompting the LLM with a set of instructions.",
    "There exist other forms of acquiring feedback, such as querying a trained feedback model or using external factual knowledge (Pan et al., 2023)."
  ]
}